### 1. One-Line Summary
Tenergy 05 is the benchmark for high-arc, high-spin looping with crisp springy power and reliable bite. K3 is a hybrid concept: tackier topsheet + stronger sponge support for heavier first-ball spin and more direct, harder-driving power when you engage.

### 2. Head-to-Head Breakdown
* **Speed & Gears:**
    * **Low Impact:**
        * Tenergy 05: More catapult and bounce at low input; easier depth with compact strokes but can feel lively in the short game.
        * K3: More dead/controlled at very low impact; requires a clearer brush/engagement to produce depth.
    * **Top End:**
        * Tenergy 05: High top speed with a strong arc; excels when you loop with full acceleration and timing.
        * K3: Very high top end on driven loops and counters; feels more like a hard, direct gear once the sponge is fully engaged.
    * **Linearity:**
        * Tenergy 05: More catapult-driven; power comes on quickly and can feel less linear if you change swing speed a lot.
        * K3: More linear and gear-separated; clearer difference between touch gear and power gear.

* **Spin Mechanics:**
    * **Opening Loop:**
        * Tenergy 05: Excellent on opening against backspin with a safer arc; forgiving when contact is slightly late.
        * K3: Very strong opener if you brush thin and engage the tacky topsheet; rewards precise upward acceleration.
    * **Max Spin:**
        * Tenergy 05: Elite peak spin, especially in fast brush-loop exchanges; high RPM with speed.
        * K3: Potentially comparable or higher heaviness (spin + weight) on slower/heavier loops, especially from mid-distance when you engage fully.
    * **Topsheet Grip:**
        * Tenergy 05: High mechanical grip; consistent across humidity but relies on quality brushing.
        * K3: Added tack + grip can hold the ball more; can be sensitive to dust/maintenance for consistent tack performance.

* **Flight Path (Throw Angle):**
    * **Arc Height:**
        * Tenergy 05: Naturally higher throw; easier net clearance and heavy arcing loop.
        * K3: Medium-high but more forward/direct when driven; arc rises more when you brush rather than hit.
    * **Safety:**
        * Tenergy 05: Higher margin over the net in opening and rally loops; safer for spin-first patterns.
        * K3: Safe when you commit to the right contact; less auto-arc, so technique consistency matters more.

* **Feel & Feedback:**
    * **Sensation:**
        * Tenergy 05: Crisp, springy, and lively; strong click feedback on clean contact.
        * K3: Firmer and more solid; feels denser with a Chinese-style bite then release.
    * **Dwell:**
        * Tenergy 05: Medium dwell with strong rebound; dwell feels short but grippy due to topsheet geometry.
        * K3: Feels like longer dwell on brush contacts; more hold on slow/heavy loops.

* **Control & Short Game:**
    * **Sensitivity:**
        * Tenergy 05: More reactive to incoming spin because of springiness; demands a cleaner touch on receive.
        * K3: Slightly calmer on passive touch shots; still spin-sensitive when tack engages, but generally easier to keep short.
    * **Touch Play:**
        * Tenergy 05: Short pushes and drops require soft hands; can pop up if youre not absorbing.
        * K3: Very good for short pushes and stop-block style receives; easier to keep low if you use the tack.

* **Blocking & Countering:**
    * **Passive Block:**
        * Tenergy 05: Stable if angle is correct, but the catapult can send blocks long if youre late/flat.
        * K3: Firmer, more damped passive block; easier to sit the ball on the table.
    * **Active Counter:**
        * Tenergy 05: Excellent counter-looping with arc; rewards brushing through the ball.
        * K3: Strong punchy counters and counter-drives; shines when you take the ball early and drive forward.

### 3. The Recommendation
* **Choose Tenergy 05 if:**
    * You win points with high-arc, spin-first topspin patterns (open-up then pressure).
    * You value plug-and-play looping consistency on a wide range of blades.
    * You counter-loop frequently and want automatic net clearance at pace.

* **Choose K3 if:**
    * You prefer a firmer, more direct impact and want heavier first-ball spin with a hybrid bite.
    * You play a forward-driving topspin game (loop-drive, counter-drive) and like a clearer power gear.
    * You want calmer touch and blocks without giving up a high ceiling when you engage.
